
* Before using ImpecBrainSeg:
 -> Make sure python 2.7 is installed with Numpy. 
    Installed by default on Ubuntu. 
    Anaconda distribution is highly recommended for MAC and Windows.
 -> Install SimpleITK for python: 
    Command line on ubuntu:      pip install SimpleITK
    Command line for Anaconda:   conda install -c https://conda.anaconda.org/simpleitk SimpleITK
    Detailed instructions: https://itk.org/Wiki/SimpleITK/GettingStarted#Python_binary_files.

* Launching ImpecBrainSeg:
 -> Go to directory ./Software/
 -> Type: 'python ImpecBrainSeg_CLI.py'
 -> Follow instructions

* Itksnap is recommended to vizualize the results
 
 

